  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <l>WHen Rome shall heare of <hi>Purgatories Knell,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>
      <hi>Nick</hi> will be curs'd with <hi>candle, book,</hi> and <hi>bell,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>His <hi>Curry-combe</hi> will be adiudg'd to fire.</l>
   <l>O happy <hi>Nick</hi> to be a <hi>Martyrs</hi> Syre!</l>
   <l>They hardly shall, whether they blesse or curse,</l>
   <l>Make <hi>Nick</hi> much better, or his <hi>lines</hi> much worse.</l>
   <l>He tooke a lucky time his <hi>booke</hi> to vent,</l>
   <l>Tis thought the <hi>Pope</hi> hath all his <hi>curses</hi> spent.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>Robert Flint, twice Maior of Queenborough.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
